      "content": {
        "title": "Limb Salvage and Reconstruction in Oncology — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Techniques preserving limb function after tumor resection including endoprosthesis, allograft, and rotationplasty.",
        "summary": "Wide margin is oncologic priority. Endoprosthesis with expandable options used in skeletally immature patients. Allograft-prosthetic composite for segmental defects."
      },
